Install Diane with dependencies on non-default platform

Install Diane with default platform (SLC4/5 - not compatible w/ Ubuntu!):

wget http://cern.ch/diane/packages/diane-install
python diane-install TRUNK
$(~/diane/install/TRUNK/bin/diane-env)

Install dependencies for your platform:

export DIANE_PLATFORM=NOPLATF
cd ~/diane/install/TRUNK/
python etc/platform-doctor.py --test
python etc/platform-doctor.py --fix


Add entries to .bashrc:
 
export DIANE_PLATFORM=NOPLATF
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=~/diane/external/omniORB/4.1.5/NOPLATF/lib/
export PYTHONPATH=~/diane/external/omniORB/4.1.5/NOPLATF/lib/python2.6/site-packages:$PYTHONPATH
 $(/diane/install/TRUNK/bin/diane-env)
